    "html":  "\u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; margin-bottom:24px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.8px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eDaily Economic Briefing\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003ch2 style=\"margin:0; font-size:20px; font-weight:700; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eThursday, 11 June 2026\u003c/h2\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap;\"\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(248,113,113,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(248,113,113,0.25); color:#f87171; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003ePPI DAY\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); color:#fbbf24; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eMOVE 78.45 Drift\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eSOFR 3.63% Healthy\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eNFCI \u0026#8722;0.490 Loose\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128202; Liquidity \u0026amp; Stress Metrics \u0026#8212; The \u0026quot;Gnosis\u0026quot; Pulse\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eCurrent regime: Loose \u0026amp; Volatile (the bullet-train transition). Fixed-income volatility is drifting around the wholesale-inflation window while broad funding conditions remain clean.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMetric\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:right; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eValue\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMarket Context\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eStatus\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eMOVE Index\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#fbbf24; font-weight:700;\"\u003e78.45\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eTerm-premium discovery is active around the May PPI release and next week\u0027s FOMC window. The drift is tactical hedging demand, not a systemic freeze.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); color:#fbbf24; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003ePremium Volatility\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eSOFR Rate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#34d399; font-weight:700;\"\u003e3.63%\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eSecured overnight funding execution remains orderly; collateral lubrication is still supportive for risk assets.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eHealthy\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eNFCI\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#60a5fa; font-weight:700;\"\u003e\u0026#8722;0.490\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eThe weekly benchmark remains pinned near expansionary extremes, keeping the macro liquidity floor intact.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eLoose\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"margin-top:16px; padding:14px 16px; background:rgba(96,165,250,0.06); border-left:3px solid #60a5fa; border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:10px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eGnosis Interpretation\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003eThe \u0026quot;Bullet Train\u0026quot; transition framework remains the operating map. MOVE at 78.45 reflects premium discovery into PPI and FOMC, while SOFR and NFCI argue against a credit-stress interpretation. Treat equity-index flushes as mechanical liquidity transfers unless funding metrics break.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128197; Economic Calendar: 2026-06-11\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eConfirmed macro windows for today\u0027s session. PPI timing is verified against BLS; weekly claims timing is verified against the Department of Labor. The draft\u0027s Monthly Budget Statement was omitted because the June release is scheduled for June 10, not June 11.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEST (US)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eGMT+8 (Local)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eImportance\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eNotes\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS May Producer Price Index\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e08:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e20:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eHigh\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eBLS confirms the May 2026 PPI release for Jun. 11 at 08:30 ET. Draft actuals were not carried forward unless confirmed after release.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS May Core PPI\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e08:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e20:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eHigh\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eCore read embedded in the BLS PPI release; watch final demand ex-food, energy and trade services for margin-pressure signals.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS Initial Jobless Claims\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e08:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e20:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#fbbf24; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium-High\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eDOL publishes weekly claims Thursdays at 08:30 ET. Draft actual value was treated as unverified pre-release and omitted.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS 30-Year Bond Reopening Auction\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e13:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e01:00 (+1)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#fbbf24; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium-High\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eTreasury\u0027s tentative auction schedule lists the 30-year bond reopening auction on Jun. 11; long-end demand matters for term-premium tone.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#127963;\u0026#65039; Geopolitical \u0026amp; Fed Watch\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eMajor Macro Horizons (PPI / FOMC)\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe PPI Window:\u003c/strong\u003e Today\u0027s 20:30 GMT+8 wholesale inflation release is the main data gate. Hot components would feed term-premium volatility first, then equity index liquidity tests.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe FOMC Shadow:\u003c/strong\u003e Markets are positioning for the June 16-17 meeting and the communication framework around any inflation surprise.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(239,68,68,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#f87171; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eTrump \u0026amp; The Iran Situation\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCeasefire Momentum:\u003c/strong\u003e The draft narrative frames back-channel talks through regional intermediaries as a stabilizing force. Treat this as narrative unless separately confirmed in live news flow.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnergy Transmission:\u003c/strong\u003e Oil remains the key inflation channel. Any renewed Strait of Hormuz premium would hit rates and index liquidity faster than headline diplomacy.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#fbbf24; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFed Chair Kevin Warsh Watch\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAI Productivity Counterweight:\u003c/strong\u003e The draft framework keeps AI-led productivity as the disinflationary offset that lets the market absorb one hot print without instantly pricing old-style tightening.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStrategic Ambiguity:\u003c/strong\u003e Any reduction in Fed speech density would increase the weight of official meeting language, so today\u0027s data matters most through how it changes June 16-17 expectations.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Matrix:\u003c/strong\u003e The May 1 breakout signature remains the technical anchor. PPI volatility should be classified as a shake-out unless breadth and funding conditions both deteriorate.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Levels:\u003c/strong\u003e Gnosis structural projections remain mapped to the year-end Wall Street High Call zone of 8,447 to 8,477.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e Around the 20:30 GMT+8 PPI window, monitor 1.5k volume charts in MotiveWave for expansionary stop-hunts. Avoid fading all-time-high expansions; buy sharp liquidity flushes into VAL only when the tape confirms absorption.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Williams Rule:\u003c/strong\u003e Keep position sizing strict into the June 16 natural-cycle date. The opportunity is structural, but the intraday path can stay disorderly while rates digest PPI.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"
